wav_file = 'echo_mixed_input_2.wav'
with wave.open(wav_file, 'rb') as wav:
  sampling_frequency = wav.getframerate()
  wav_params = wav.getparams()
  input_data = wav.readframes(wav.getnframes())
  input_data = np.frombuffer(input_data, dtype=np.int16).astype(np.float32)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
x = np.arange(np.size(input_data)) / sampling_frequency 
plt.plot(x, input_data)
plt.xlabel('Time [second]')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')
plt.show()

エコーキャンセリング¶

NLMS
$y[n] = \sum_{k=0}^{K-1}\hat{h}_{\rm old}[k]x[n-k]$
$e[n] = z[n] - y[n]$
$\hat{h}_{\rm new} = \hat{h}_{\rm old} + \frac{\mu}{\sum_{k=0}^{K-1}(x[n-k])^{2}+\epsilon}e[n]x[n-k]$

$n$$k$
$x[n]$reference_data
$\hat{h}_{\rm old}[k]$$\hat{h}_{\rm new}[k]$estimated_rir $K$oldnew
$y[n]$estimated_echo
$z[n]$input_data
$e[n]$erroroutput_data
$\mu$NLMSmyu
$\epsilon$1e-10

In [23]:
K = 1024

myu = 1.0

stop_update_time = 10.0

eps = 1e-10

NLMS

In [24]:
# (input_data)
N = np.size(input_data)
# 
estimated_rir = np.zeros(K)
# 
output_data = np.zeros(N)

for n in range(N):
  if n-K+1 < 0:
    # n-K+1<0
    # 
    output_data[n] = input_data[n]
  else:
    #
    # NLMS
    #

    # 
    # 
    # 07_02_convolve_rir.ipynb
    reference_part = reference_data[n-K+1:n+1]
    reference_rev = np.flip(reference_part)
    estimated_echo = np.dot(estimated_rir, reference_rev)

    # 
    # (error)
    output_data[n] = input_data[n] - estimated_echo
    error = output_data[n]

    # ()  
    norm = np.sum(reference_rev**2) + eps

    # (stop_update_time * sampling_rate)
    # 
    if n < stop_update_time * sampling_frequency:
      estimated_rir += (myu / norm) * error * reference_rev

# (input_data)
N = np.size(input_data)
# 
estimated_rir = np.zeros(K)
# 
output_data = np.zeros(N)

for n in range(N):
  if n-K+1 < 0:
    # n-K+1<0
    # 
    output_data[n] = input_data[n]
  else:
    #
    # NLMS
    #

    # 
    # 
    # 07_02_convolve_rir.ipynb
    reference_part = reference_data[n-K+1:n+1]
    reference_rev = np.flip(reference_part)
    estimated_echo = np.dot(estimated_rir, reference_rev)

    # 
    # (error)
    output_data[n] = input_data[n] - estimated_echo
    error = output_data[n]

    # ()  
    norm = np.sum(reference_rev**2) + eps

    # (stop_update_time * sampling_rate)
    # 
    if (n < stop_update_time * sampling_frequency) or (n > 13.0 * sampling_frequency and n < 15.0 * sampling_frequency) or (n > 18.0 * sampling_frequency and n < 20.0 * sampling_frequency):
      estimated_rir += (myu / norm) * error * reference_rev
